OL,6,FThey fought the manufacturer and the
OL,7,Fgovernment for recognition and
OL,8,Fcompensation, something reflected in
OL,9,Fthe play.
OL,11,F"It's an uplifting story," explained
OL,12,Fwriter Steve Bird.
OL,14,F"It's a story of someone who wants to
OL,15,Fjust go out there and fight for the
OL,16,Fright to be a normal person. Gary did
OL,17,Fit. His mother certainly pushed him
OL,18,Ftowards that."
